<h2>Categories + Customers Intersection Table</h2>
<br>

{{!-- Create a table --}}
<table id="drinkCategoriesCustomers-table">

  {{!-- Header section --}}
  <thead>

    {{!-- For just the first row, we print each key of the row object as a header cell so we
    know what each column means when the page renders --}}
    <tr>
      {{#each data.[0]}}
      <th>
        {{@key}}
      </th>
      {{/each}}
    </tr>
  </thead>

  {{!-- Body section --}}
  <tbody>

    {{!-- For each row, print info in order --}}
    {{#each data}}
    <tr data-value={{this.drinkCategoriesCustomersID}}>
      <td>{{this.drinkCategoriesCustomersID}}</td>
      <td>{{this.drinkCategoryID}}</td>
      <td>{{this.customerID}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/each}}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p>CRUD Functionality for this Intersection table is handled on the "Customers" Page.</p>
<p>A bit of explanation: Customers must have a preferred drink category, so it's not possible</p>
<p>to have a null value. Deleting the customer deletes the above relationship.</p>
